			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Two of your items pop out at me needing immediate replacement: The Gnollish Ring of Sorcery, and the Arcane Belt of Ken.
<br />

<br />
The Gnollish Ring of Sorcery can easily be replaced by any number of rings.  An easy one to get would be the <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=24202" target="_blank" class="postlink">The ring of Hardened Ash</a> out of the Takish Hiz dungeons.  I have seen that ring drop every 10 Takish Hiz adventures or so, as well as other level-appropriate ring (like <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=24006" target="_blank" class="postlink">Faience Ring of Delusions</a>.  If you want something a bit more challenging and a bit nicer, <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=17090" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Band of the Visionary</a> is out of the IC in PoV from a rare spawn (Sleepwalker), and that camp will net you some nice AAXP while you are there.
<br />

<br />
I had an idea about the waist item: <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=8715" target="_blank" class="postlink">Strands of Power</a> from a named worm in AC.  It should be doable with a good group, or, a mini-raid.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1071902" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Whazy Weemage</a>, Arch Convoker, Holder of the Orb, Master Brewer
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1072169" target="_blank" class="postlink"> Druish Swiftfoot</a>, Bearer of Nature Walkers Scimitar and Fabulous
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1072747" target="_blank" class="postlink">Supmusic Yortsed</a>, Enemy to all Paladins
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Maelin Starpyre</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
